  "rationale": "The 'How we work' section follows Finsweet's 6-layer Client-First hierarchy, ensuring a robust and scalable structure. A Grid layout is used for the main component with an asymmetrical 1fr to 1.5fr split to balance the heading and the step list. The step cards are organized in a 2x2 grid, each utilizing absolute positioning for the background shape to create a layered indicator effect. All dimensions, spacing, and typography are defined in 'rem' units for fluid responsiveness. The design leverages pre-defined typography classes (heading-style-h2, heading-style-h5, text-style-paragraph) and color variables (color--grey, color--dark-blue, color--royal-blue) from the design system to ensure architectural consistency. Spacing wrappers (margin-bottom) handle vertical gaps between elements, and object-fit: contain is applied to icons/shapes as per MAS-V2-003 to prevent distortion."
